        Forschungsumgebung / beta maṣāḥǝft Brill Felber Brill,  IslHornAfr: Islam in the Horn of Africa, A Comparative Literary Approach. European Research Council (Advanced Grant no. 322849)</dc:publisher><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu"/><dcterms:bibliographicCitation>PRS0043IHA</dcterms:bibliographicCitation><dc:format>xml</dc:format><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">en</dc:language><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">ar</dc:language><dc:contributor>Alessandro Gori</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>P. Bearman, Th. Bianquis, C.E. Bosworth, E. van Donzel, W.P. Heinrichs</dc:contributor><foaf:gender>male</foaf:gender><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/ontology/pers"/><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">البوصيري شرف الدين ابو عبد الله محمد بن سعيد بن حماد الصنهاجي</foaf:name><foaf:name>al-Būṣīrī, Šaraf al-Dīn Abū ʻAbd Allāh Muḥammad b. Saʻīd b.  Ḥammād al-Ṣanhāǧī</foaf:name><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E67_Birth"/><crm:P78_is_identified_by>0608-10-01 </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E69_Death"/><crm:P78_is_identified_by>0694 </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><crm:P78_is_identified_by>7th /13th centuryEgyptian poet of Berber origin, he was a skilled calligrapher, a traditionist and a celebrated reciter of the Qurʾān, but his name has been immortalised by the Burda ode.  He followed the courses of the Ṣūfī Abu al-ʿAbbās Aḥmad al-Mursī (d. 686/1287) and was also involved in the first developments of the Šāḏiliyya order
               </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span></rdf:Description><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA/place/annotation/1"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC0013IHA"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>Alexandria / al-Iskandariyya</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA/place/annotation/2"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC0030IHA"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>Bilbeis / Bilbays</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA/place/annotation/3"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC0031IHA"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>Būṣīr</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA/place/annotation/4"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC0026IHA"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>Mecca / Makka al-Mukarrama</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation><oa:Annotation rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA/place/annotation/5"><oa:hasTarget rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS0043IHA"/><oa:hasBody rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC0029IHA"/><oa:annotatedAt rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-05+02:00</oa:annotatedAt><lawd:hasName>Medina / al-Madīna al-Munawwara</lawd:hasName></oa:Annotation></rdf:RDF>